Huum... What? I was addicted at.. Fall Guys 2? Yes, the game it's funny and cool. You can waste a lot of your time here, if you have friends to play, it's so much better. I just was sad at the fact you need to get the battle pass to use some powers, but, the game is very funny.

Jogo multiplayer ou sozinho, típico jogo para alcançar a vitória passando por mapas, um jogo curto viciante que é muito recomendado, não é muito difícil aprender os comandos dos jogos porque são os comandos normais.

i have complaints

This game initially puts you against bots, as Obscure has said in the review's comments. Only to then put you against actual players and show you its harsh p2w reality.

This game is luck based as fuck, the place you spawn at in the last round will often tell you if you're gonna win or not.

Extending on the pay to win factor... The three special emotes are so unfair that it's not even fun to play this game if you don't have them. having only ONE of them can give you a win that you would have otherwise lost with the click of a button. And yes, i did fact check this.

The community is also trash.

Don't play, please. Take it from me, i suffered so you don't have to. I wish i could take this off my profile and never ever play it again.

[h1] WARNING! [/h1]

[u] Game with Pay to Win features [/u]

The season pass (included in the Steam version but not in the mobile version) has in its last place, emotes that give advantage and affect the gameplay, such as kicking or hitting other players.
So you will have advantage over mobile players who do not have the pass and all players who have not managed to complete the pass, this also forces you to complete the pass before the end of the season to get that emote, in other words, grind the season pass.
Photo of the actual "Special Emote": https://i.gyazo.com/096c686a950e0224e9115314740fab28.png
